<subSubSection id="DBE94F2CDF1E0520657272862BD9778C" pageId="null" pageNumber="169" type="vernacular_names">
<paragraph id="59AFEB421CCC8E886B892A02CA41935F" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">Berg-Steinkresse</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</title>
<subSubSection id="4AD62EFA376EC18FF1300D2EE5495B27" pageId="null" pageNumber="169" type="description">
<paragraph id="19076E685D9422439AFA6FAE901A3EAE" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">
Unterscheidet sich von 
<taxonomicName id="53626E955A0EC306C364D8FDE81C3A10" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Thlaspi" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="null" pageNumber="169" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="alpestre">
<emphasis id="A0EF644E6C0EEF8BAF09C609807797F8" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">A. alpestre</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Nr. 3) durch folgende Merkmale: Bis 25 cm hoch; 
<normalizedToken id="6F1AC71F8C90E49BE38964AC19DECCFB" originalValue="Blätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">Blaetter</normalizedToken>
bis 2,5 cm lang, 2-8mal so lang wie breit; 
<normalizedToken id="C75C556EB965814E54F65206488531D2" originalValue="Kelchblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">Kelchblaetter</normalizedToken>
2,5-3,5 mm lang; 
<emphasis id="3284A0C2EB3002B80CC0C2F74B4A8A96" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">
<normalizedToken id="33467BB0D1374725847F643BE07B3949" originalValue="Kronblätter" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">Kronblaetter</normalizedToken>
4-6 mm lang, vorn ausgerandet; Staubbeutel 0,6-0,8 mm lang;
</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="ACF4ACF54AE8CA6E2E11ADE755CCB23C" originalValue="Früchte" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">Fruechte</normalizedToken>
an 
<emphasis id="7E9C5DBCDC53890989E05C546A5C4925" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">6-10 mm langem Stiel</emphasis>
, 4-6 mm lang (ohne Griffel) und 3,5-5,5 mm breit, 
<emphasis id="B5DCD31C081B3BC9BB5E3EAFDAD6B5F9" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">mit 2-3 mm langem Griffel</emphasis>
, 2-4samig. - 
<normalizedToken id="003225338E8AEA88C2F991AE991EC0DE" originalValue="Blüte" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">Bluete</normalizedToken>
: 
<normalizedToken id="6C94D0940ECDA8236410AB3DC2095CC2" originalValue="Frühling" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">Fruehling</normalizedToken>
und 
<normalizedToken id="229C30C86C92667F44BAD20E5D181867" originalValue="früher" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">frueher</normalizedToken>
Sommer.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6F8C2D22A9753586046CBA65D3313602" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">
<emphasis id="6CFDA33E9708EC55DDB34788D2CBE9AF" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">Zytologische Angaben. 2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="8FFA64C0E3603004E6ABDFB30916375D" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">16:</emphasis>
Material aus botanischem Garten (Jaretzky 1932, Manton 1932), aus dem Atlas (Quezel 1957). 
<emphasis id="A2D1F04F877407BF2AE0D67AB0FCA8EF" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">2n</emphasis>
= 
<emphasis id="06F867D48BAAB223A8B82FE47A219DBD" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">32:</emphasis>
Material aus Ungarn (
<normalizedToken id="9FA4A8706C713C08B3A644BFB32544B4" originalValue="Böcher" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">Boecher</normalizedToken>
und Larsen 1958).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7118D2C825C66D3D5BAD9EFAF3D76AA8" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">
<emphasis id="D3BB047E11E4FBD34209BAF2BD3126B8" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">Standort.</emphasis>
Kollin, montan und subalpin. Trockene, offene, basenreiche, steinige 
<normalizedToken id="156D7E0A54A49AF2B1FC3902A62216CB" originalValue="Böden" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">Boeden</normalizedToken>
in warmen Lagen. Trokkenrasen, felsige 
<normalizedToken id="86C0F249823E6670EC0F70E0B59D4E74" originalValue="Hänge" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">Haenge</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3D0447698D6060915151466F7B7352DD" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">
<emphasis id="454BA30ECDE333AA835A962252D97E7C" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">Verbreitung. Mediterrane Pflanze:</emphasis>
<normalizedToken id="9FD135DD1E8B2D929D258D24FAB8EFB2" originalValue="Südliches" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">Suedliches</normalizedToken>
Europa (
<normalizedToken id="1E74DCC6A595771D5FFAC7CC5910B59B" originalValue="nordwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">nordwaerts</normalizedToken>
vereinzelt bis Paris, Harz, untere Weichsel); Kleinasien; Nordafrika. Verbreitungskarte von Meusel et al. (1965). Das nahe verwandte 
<taxonomicName id="2C1B58B0D907DE088F091F1DD02446A3" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Alyssum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="null" pageNumber="169" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gmelinii">
<emphasis id="964D8F69B4FE2411BB6BA45105306CBA" italics="true" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">A. Gmelinii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Jordan in Osteuropa (
<normalizedToken id="AD480308E777AA22719F67BC59CDBB2F" originalValue="westwärts" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">westwaerts</normalizedToken>
bis Mainz). - Im Gebiet: Jura (
<normalizedToken id="72536F08EA487AD410CD4E7CA25D5285" originalValue="Dép" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">Dep</normalizedToken>
. Ain [Bugey], 
<normalizedToken id="173044DCA1452BA4934D68BED51B2EE3" originalValue="Dép" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">Dep</normalizedToken>
. Jura [Arbois, Champagnole], 
<normalizedToken id="C4D693CF17CCC8A1374FF09B86A27DD4" originalValue="Dôle" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">Dole</normalizedToken>
[angepflanzt], Grendelfluh bei Olten, Basler und 
<normalizedToken id="7ADCC24866330272459E57CE0A0D808A" originalValue="Elsässer" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">Elsaesser</normalizedToken>
Jura, 
<normalizedToken id="DC4D60F19CD022FF2BCE90C2F4044FDA" originalValue="Lägern" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">Laegern</normalizedToken>
); Burgdorf; Oberrheinische Tiefebene (Kaiserstuhl, Isteiner Klotz), Hegau (Hohentwiel, 
<normalizedToken id="E9B64A43CF90E111BE600DC191536F99" originalValue="Hohenhöwen" pageId="null" pageNumber="169">Hohenhoewen</normalizedToken>
); Maurienne (Lanslebourg-Mont Cenis), Tarentaise (Col de la Galise); Wallis (Ganter am Simplon); Aostatal (Gebiet von Cogne, Valsavaranche).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
